job_description:
Not just another start-up, we fight fraud!

At Shift Technology we are proud to have a purpose: to help insurers weed out claims corruption. Our SaaS solution, which leverages Big Data and AI, has been used to unravel fraud networks across Asia, Europe, and the Americas.
If you are someone motivated by meaningful work, Shift Technology may just be the spot for you!

Your day-to-day

At Shift Technology, we are constantly looking for new ways to innovate. Fraud landscapes are in constant motion and in order to ensure our detection methods are always one step ahead, our data scientists must be too.
Shift Technology data scientists are the central productive force of the company. They design the models, construct the features, implement the rules, and optimize the algorithms that are used throughout the data processing pipeline. They face two main challenges: messy and often incomplete data paired with complex and ever-evolving problems.
The data we collect comes in all shapes and sizes and is not, for the most part, quantitative. Insurance claims data typically includes date, location, circumstantial details, damage descriptions, and involved parties. With that wide array of information, our data scientists must be comfortable with a variety of specific approaches: unsupervised anomaly detection, temporal sequences analysis, semantic network analysis …
As for the solution, our data scientists must be able to produce predictions justified with intelligible explanations, even when very little data is available.
Our data scientists have the exciting mission of designing and implementing models that replicate and enhance real-world fraud handling deduction patterns. They are tasked with optimizing the algorithms involved in the data processing pipeline and making adjustments as fraud scenarios mature and evolve.
After a few short months of joining our data scientist team you will be able to:
Understand insurance data and fraud mechanisms;
Create the associated mathematical models;
Implement, test and optimize the associated algorithms;
Participate in workshops with the clients to gather feedback and integrate it to the models;
Continuously provide ideas to improve the solution.
Your toolkit

On the job you will be asked to code in C# so programming experience is a big advantage, but not essential if you are willing to learn fast!

Your profile

Shift Technologys data science department is filled with top performers who are committed to technical excellence, inspired by challenging projects, and always on the look-out for new learning opportunities.
If the following qualities ring true, you would fit right in at Shift Technology:
You have advanced technical skills in Applied Mathematics, preferably in machine learning and/or operations research;
You combine strong analysis with synthesis abilities and are not afraid to deal with the details;
You can write quality production code;
You don't mind meeting with clients to discuss their needs and integrate their feedback in your projects;
You are bilingual in English !

Duties & Responsibilities

Position Overview:
The Research Associate will provide research and execution support to the Editor-in-Chief of the Harvard Data Science Review, a new journal and digital platform that will launch in 2018-2019 academic year. The HDSR aims to be the leading platform for all aspects of data science, from its disciplinary foundations to societal impact and policy implications; from state-of-the-art methodologies and technologies to emerging opportunities and challenges; and from professional ethics to public understanding. The HDSR will pioneer new models of digital outreach through open publishing and close engagement with the HDSI’s educational mission, with an emphasis on multimedia dissemination, learner-oriented visualization, author-reader interaction, and establishing a global presence.

Principal Duties and Responsibilities (Essential Functions*):
Reporting to the Editor-in-Chief of the HDSR, the Research Associate will conduct research that aims to establish HDSR as a new kind of digital forum that reflects the synergistic nature of Data Science, providing a crossroads at which fundamental Data Science research and education intersect directly with societally impactful applications from industry, governments, NGOs, and others. In particular, the Research Associate is expected to undertake initiatives to investigate and establish a cutting-edge digital platform that unites the strengths of a premier research journal, a cutting-edge educational publication, and a popular magazine; a platform that can enhance reader’s learning experiences via interactive presentations and on-line education modules, as well as data science research replicability and reproducibility by maintaining appropriate data and codes that permit readers and researchers to verify, experiment, and explore.

The Research Associate is expected to carry out a variety duties to support the Editor-in-Chief, including:

Research, compare and evaluate major existing digital forums and platforms in Data Science and related fields, including their business models;
Research strategies and solutions for integrating and enhancing existing digital forums and related multimedia platforms with the goal of building an all-encompassing digital forum to achieve HDSR’s mission;
Research the state-of-the art of platforms that promote interactive reader experiences, especially those that are data-science oriented, and identify and implement a suitable platform for HDSR;
Research major existing databases and data curation and provenance platforms that enhance research reproducibility, replicability and triangulation;
Research and make recommendations related to partnership models that will foster mutually beneficial relationships between a journal-based digital forum and on-line education platforms, such as HarvardX;
Research strategies and models for engaging authors to turn their publications into pedagogical materials and products, suitable for on-line or residential education;
Research strategies and digital models for engaging and sustaining wide-ranging readership and subscribers (institutional and individual; printed and online) of HDSR;
Research and assist in the implementation of a financially sustainable business model for the HDSR digital forum
Prepare communications and other documents, such as presentation slides, promotion materials, funding proposals, etc.
Other emerging research topics and duties as identified and required by the launching of HDSR.

Basic Qualifications

Candidates MUST meet the following basic qualifications in order to be considered for this role:

A Master’s degree in information, library, and/or data science research, and a minimum of five years of relevant research experience.

Additional Qualifications

Successful candidate must be a self-starter with strong interpersonal skills and an entrepreneurial spirit. Must be comfortable with multi-tasking and working in a deadline-driven environment. Must be exceptionally organized and detail-oriented. Should be comfortable with change and an evolving organizational structure – both the HDSI and HDSR are growing and the ability to work as part of a small, highly productive team is very important. Ph.D. level of study or research preferred. Editorial experience preferred. Demonstrated strong written and oral communication skills, and the ability to independently conduct research and make sound judgments. Demonstrated digital competence and expertise.
